node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

node.text:
Real life fairytale village 🌿 Would you visit Lauterbrunnen?

This picturesque village is located in the Swiss alps. Fringed by rocky cliffs, vibrant greens and waterfalls, this spot is one of the most impressive valleys of the area. ⛰️

Insider tip: Although it’s mostly known as an expansive skiing spot during winter, Lauterbrunnen is just as pretty during summer (and it’s perfect for hiking!).

📍Lauterbrunnen, Switzerland

🇨🇭 #discoverSwitzerland with @thetravelergene

A complete underwater world 🤿 Would you dive around here?

You can find the world’s deepest pool at Deep Dive Dubai. Open to both first time divers and professionals, this record-breaking, 60m deep pool resembles the coolest, sunken city 🤯

📍Dubai, United Arab Emirates

🇦🇪 #discoverUnitedArabEmirates with the Crown Prince of Dubai @faz3, and @deepdivedubai

#discoverearth with @brodiemoss

Nordic wonderland with @jj.trailwalker 😍🇮🇸 Obsessed with the beauty of Iceland

Iceland is a truly one of a kind place that’s on so many bucket lists. Getting front-row seats to the magical Northern lights, unwinding in the region’s geothermal pools or discovering majestic volcanoes…Iceland has so much to offer!

📍Iceland

🇮🇸 #discoverIceland with @jj.trailwalker

node.text:
Pure magic ✨📚 You can find this surreal bookstore in  Dujiangyan Zhongshuge, located in Chengdu, China. This two-story bookstore was designed by architecture firm X+Living, and is a true wonderland for book lovers. C-shaped bookshelves and mirrored ceilings give off an extended, almost never-ending illusion. Would you spend the day here?

📍Dujiangyan Zhongshuge, China

🇨🇳 #discoverChina with @xlivingart

node.text:
Phyllium giganteum lifecycle with @insecthaus_adi 🍃

Phyllium giganteum is a very wide and large leaf insect with a body shaped like a leaf. Also the legs have appendages making it look like leaves. In nature it can be found in tropical forests in Malaysia. This species consists of only females.

#discoverearth with @insecthaus_adi

A day in Iceland’s glass lodge with @reneeroaming✨ Who would you take to this dreamy cabin?

Insider tip: If you’d like to catch Iceland’s famous midnight sun, the best time to visit is between May and July – and the further north you go, the more nights of midnight sun you’ll get!

📍@panoramaglasslodge, Iceland

🇮🇸 #discoverIceland with @reneeroaming

node.text:
Adventurer’s paradise in Wadi Rum, Jordan ✨🏜️ Who would you escape to here with?

Wadi Rum (also known as the Valley of the Moon), is a mesmerizing, protected area nestled within Jordan’s desert. Dotted with beautiful camping spots such as this one, Wadi Rum is perfect if you’re looking to explore the region’s desert.

📍Wadi Rum, Jordan

🇯🇴 #discoverJordan with @ludoc

Would you go for a swim with this curious turtle? 🐢

#discoverearth with @jacintashackleton
